==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Puke
<hw>Puke</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Puked</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Puking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. G. <ets>spucken</ets> to
spit, and E. <ets>spew</ets>.]</ety> <def>To eject the contests of the
stomach; to vomit; to spew.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The infant⟦br⟧
Mewling and <qex>puking</qex> in the nurse's arms.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puke</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Puke
<hw>Puke</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To eject from the stomach; to vomit
up.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puke</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Puke
<hw>Puke</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A medicine that causes vomiting; an
emetic; a vomit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puke</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Puke
<hw>Puke</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Etymol. uncertain.]</ety> <def>Of a
color supposed to be between black and russet.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This color has by some been regarded as the same with
<xex>puce</xex>; but Nares questions the identity.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puker</ent>⟦br⟧
